manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Clicky mechanical blue switch gaming keyboard for ultimate gaming performance. The mechanical keyboard keys offer medium resistance, audible click sound & tactile feedback. Fn+F1: Media Player, Fn+F2: Volume -, Fn+F3: Volume +, Fn+F4: Mute,Fn+F5: Halt, Fn+F6: Previous song, Fn+F7: Play/Suspend, Fn+F8: Next Song, Fn+F9: E-mail, Fn+f10: Homepage, Fn+F11: My computer, Fn+F12: Calculator. This mechanical blue switch gaming keyboard has multiple lighting modes. You can select the one lighting effect you want, and change the brightness and speed.
Keyboard size: 17.09*4.93*1.34 inches Keyboard weight: about 840g Connection: wired Wire Length: about 1.5m Number of keys: 104

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fun keyboard, cool lights
reviews.reviewText: I love the retro look of this keyboard. The lights are cool and when you press the FN key with any of the other keys next to the number pad, you can change the pattern of the lights. Coolest thing ever, and the keys are raised so it's easier to type. Makes a sharp clickety-clack sound, almost like an old fashioned typewriter when you type, love it! I debated whether or not to order this keyboard but it turned out to be a great decision, haha!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This is beyond why I was expecting. I was skeptical about getting the typical white with the blue light that is all over Amazon, and didn’t want an assortment of colors either. When I saw this gold light I knew it was the one. When I opened the box which was well packaged, it was prettier than I expected. The keys are all in a rose gold casing and they have the most amazing clicking sound to them. Far better than my previous typewriter keyboard set. This looks and feels expensive before plugging in. Once unplugged it in all the lights danced around and then I played with the light options a bit. You’ll see the lights flashing in the video- it’s due to recording it, and does not do that to the naked eye. The gold light is perfect and gives that warm vibe versus the cold blue lights I’ve been seeing on other keyboards. Great buy, highly recommend to jazz up your desk and workspace.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love this keyboard!
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love this keyboard! It makes me feel like I am typing on diamonds. :-) The amount of click is perfect as is the amount of tension in the keys. The only reason I gave it 4 stars instead of 3 is because my first one stopped working correctly after just less than a year. Also, my second one came with several of the keys unattached. It was easy to pop them back on though. If this one goes out, I will be repurchasing again. That's how much I love it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I love it, but it's already failing.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this keyboard toward the end of October this year. I love the colors, I love the rippling as I type, I love the clicky-clack, I love the look. BUT after just a couple months of use, the U key is acting up - sometimes doubling the time it takes to type because I have to pay attention to my spelling. Sometimes the U will simply not type, sometimes it'll type uu after one press. Really disappointing because this is overall a really nice keyboard. But it's not even been two months.

Used daily for 8 months. Loved everything about it. Super clicky, great colour options but just stopped working the “W” command locked on and it just types on its own. It was perfect and everything I wanted. It just only lasted 8 months

reviews.reviewTitle: If you need the clicky sounds this keyboard got you
reviews.reviewText: This is a great keyboard for those who like the visual and audio appeal with their keyboards.It gives a very satisfying click and with the changeable light settings there are options for everyone.Though it is a bit tall which can be rough on the wrists without a wrist rest.And the smooth circular shape of the keys makes it easy to push the wrong key, so you will need practice with it before using it to game.I honestly love it but that is because I need that audio and visual serotonin boast it creates to keep me motivated and focused. If you also like those things I would recommend this for you.

The assembly is heavy and solid.The keystroke action is that of IBM (in the begining)It's adequate for typing in a dark enviromentThe lettering of the individual keys be SHOULD CENTEREDwith LED Light passing through each key.The individual keys only light ONE colour with each row of keyshaving a different colour .The colours are good and light show is entertaining ,but I'm not a kid anymore .
